  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We construct Q-operators for the open spin- <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> XXX Heisenberg spin chain with diagonal boundary matrices. The Q-operators are defined as traces over an infinite-dimensional auxiliary space involving novel types of reflection operators derived from the boundary Yang–Baxter equation. We argue that the Q-operators defined in this way are polynomials in the spectral parameter and show that they commute with transfer matrix. Finally, we prove that the Q-operators satisfy Baxter's TQ-equation and derive the explicit form of their eigenvalues in terms of the Bethe roots.</subfield>
